setSetting

public void setSetting(java.lang.String name,
                       java.lang.String value)
Sets the setting 'name' to 'value'. Settings end up as xml attributes so they store various attributes of an element. Note that the description of an element is also stored as a setting, however, the description is actually not saved as an xml attribute but a separate node.
